results.name: Expansion of Product_{m>=1} (1 - m*q^m)^4.
comment: This sequence is obtained from the generalized Euler transform in A266964 by taking f(n) = -4, g(n) = n. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Dec 29 2017
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
formula: G.f.: exp(-4*Sum_{j>=1} Sum_{k>=1} k^j*x^(j*k)/j). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Feb 07 2018
program: (PARI) m=50; q='q+O('q^m); Vec(prod(n=1,m,(1-n*q^n)^4)) \\ _G. C. Greubel_, Feb 23 2018
(MAGMA) Coefficients(&*[(1-m*x^m)^4:m in [1..40]])[1..40] where x is PolynomialRing(Integers()).1; // _G. C. Greubel_, Feb 23 2018
